title: Mets vs. Chicago Cubs lineups: The one that clinches a World Series berth?
text:
Comments 
CHICAGO â€” Is this the starting lineup that sends the Mets to the World Series? 
They hold a 3-0 lead entering Game 4 of the National League Championship Series on Wednesday night at Wrigley Field. They'll have Steven Matz on the mound , while the Cubs go with Jason Hammel and their entire bullpen. 
The Mets and manager Terry Collins will use with the same starting lineup as Game 3. That worked well enough for a 5-2 win. 
One more win and the Mets get to wait until Tuesday, Oct. 27, for Game 1 of the World Series. Wow.
